  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nI'm trying to query sync committees via the api. My node is fully synced and not reporting any errors. Unfortunately I sometimes get an error `nil summary returned from the DB`. After looking around a bit, it seems like this only happens for epochs which have a missing first block. Example epochs are:\r\n`74297, 80553, 88928, 89856, 98652`\r\nAs discussed in discord, I `may have just the block in db that orphaned` (though I didn't test this). `This looks like a bug in the reporting of optimistic sync status.`\r\n\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nI made this small python script for testing:\r\n<pre><code>\r\nimport requests\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nurl = \"http://192.168.178.48:3500\"\r\n\r\ndef GetSyncCommittee():\r\n    epoch = 74297 # 74297, 80553, 88928, 89856, 98652\r\n    dependent_root = json.loads(requests.get(url + \"/eth/v1/validator/duties/proposer/\" + str(epoch)).content)[\"dependent_root\"]\r\n    state_root = json.loads(requests.get(url + \"/eth/v1/beacon/headers/\" + dependent_root).content)[\"data\"][\"header\"][\"message\"][\"state_root\"]\r\n    print(requests.get(url + \"/eth/v1/beacon/states/\" + state_root + \"/sync_committees?epoch=\" + str(epoch)).content)\r\n\r\n\r\nGetSyncCommittee()\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nb'{\"message\":\"Could not check if slot\\'s block is optimistic: could not check if block is optimistic: nil summary returned from the DB\",\"code\":500}'\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nDebian GNU/Linux 11 (bullseye)\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nv2.1.2\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n",
